==Abstract==

This IIP specifies DNS-based node discovery for Lightning, adapted from BOLT #10.

==Specification==

===DNS Seed Format===

<pre>
<network>.<seed-domain>
</pre>

Networks: ln (mainnet), lnt (testnet)

===Record Types===

====SRV Records====

<pre>
_lightning._tcp.ln.seed.example.com. IN SRV 10 10 2216 node1.example.com.
</pre>

====TXT Records====

<pre>
ln.seed.example.com. IN TXT "ln1qp...xyz@192.168.1.1:2216"
</pre>

===Node ID Encoding===

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Network !! HRP
|-
| Mainnet || ln
|-
| Testnet || lnt
|-
| Signet || lns
|-
| Regtest || lnrt
|}

===Address Formats===

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Type !! Format
|-
| IPv4 || a.b.c.d:port
|-
| IPv6 || [addr]:port
|-
| Tor v3 || addr.onion:port
|-
| I2P || addr.b32.i2p:port
|}

===DNS Seeds===

Mainnet:
* ln.seed1.international-coin.org
* ln.seed2.international-coin.org

Testnet:
* lnt.seed1.international-coin.org
* lnt.seed2.international-coin.org

===TXT Record Chunking===

For large node IDs (2592 bytes), split across multiple TXT strings.

==Security Considerations==

* Seeds SHOULD support DNSSEC
* Cross-reference multiple seeds
* Verify node reachability

